Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 409<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/11/02 8:24:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15800.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nice..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Reading about some of these changes such as the line of sight and range alterations make me sick. These are no-brainer changes they should've made 3 years ago.<br>
<br>
Duh... anybody home?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I wouldn't be so harsh on VI.  I always assumed the line of sight and range things were the way they were to avoid exploits.<br>
<br>
How hard would it be to root a mob on one side of a corner, whack them, and when they start casting, run around the corner out of line of sight?  In some places you can probably take advantage of bad pathing to get out of line of sight at will, even without root.<br>
<br>
Similar things could be done for range messages.  I would expect this change will make it a lot easier for folks like druids to do things like root-dot casters.  Root the mob, run out of casting range at SoW speed.  Step into casting range to apply dots when needed, step back out of casting range to avoid being hit.<br>
<br>
We could probably &quot;joust&quot; casters on horseback to similar effect--how hard will it be to get out of casting range by the time their spell is ready to land?  I've noticed most of the really high damage spells have relatively long casting times...<br>
<br>
There are people who play this game that are a lot more creative than me, these are just a few examples of things you might be able to use as new tactics once these changes go into effect.<br>
<br>
Overall I applaud VI for looking at this closely and trying to strike the right balance.  I remember when I was low level and the mantra was always &quot;kill the caster first&quot; when you had multiple mobs because if you didn't you were in trouble.  At the high end, before these changes, casters were usually the wimps of the bunch. <p><BR>
