Seventh Cavalry<BR>
Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 419<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/11/02 1:12:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15800.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nice..</span><hr size=1> Does anyone know if channeling is based on a per hit basis?  For example, if I'm hit once during spell casting, do I have a greater chance of channeling through on the cast than if I was hit 5 times?<br>
<br>
In other words, does getting hit just turn on some sort of flag that says &quot;check against channeling for this cast&quot;, or does it do an interrupt check with every hit?<br>
<br>
If it is per hit, I would be interested to see how these changes will affect raid mobs.  If you have a Fear raid with 3-4 groups beating on a mob, that could be a lot of channeling rolls he'd have to pass to get a spell off.<br>
<br>
I assume they could find a way to tune raid mobs differently than exp mobs to account for that though, by adjusting channeling skill or whatever.<br>
<br>
For mobs that can be stunned, I expect stuns would still be a more reliable way of interrupting. <p><BR>
